data.description: Lovely renovated townhome with tons of space and light! 4 levels of living space with great flexibility and lots of recent updates. Entry level with bedroom and full bath leads to attached 1 car rear garage with convenient extra storage space. Main level with great flow, gleaming hardwood floors and high ceilings. Gourmet eat-in kitchen with granite counters, center island, stainless steel appliances and breakfast bar. The upper levels feature brand new plush carpeting, and encompass 2 additional bedrooms - both with ensuite bathes - plus a great landing area that makes a perfect reading/playroom or home office. The private rear deck provides outdoor enjoyment and is perfect for your next cookout. Located in Fort Lincoln, which was named after a Civil War-era fort constructed in 1861 to protect the nation's capital during the war. Running alongside the neighborhood is Route 50, a commuter corridor connecting 100,000 people to the greater Washington, Maryland, and Virginia area. Close to Dakota Crossing, a fantastic shopping center with tons of retail options. Costco, Lowe’s, Dick’s Sporting Goods, Marshalls, PetSmart, and much more, all within 1 mile. A stone’s throw to Fort Lincoln park, a Civil War historic site with play areas and great views. So much to love!
